## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/**usernamehere**/job-advertisement-portal.git
cd Job-Advertisement-Portal
```

### 2️⃣ Install Dependencies
#### Frontend:
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm start
```
#### Backend:
```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm run dev
```

### 3️⃣ Set Up Environment Variables
Create a `.env` file in the backend directory and configure database & API keys.

### 4️⃣ Run the Project
Start both the frontend and backend servers, then visit `http://localhost:3000`.

